We all love a cheesy Valentine’s day post. Pun intended. We’ll be celebrating today at @neptunebournemouth eating these heart-shaped Neufchâtel cheeses with fresh bread and a few glasses of our local Luberon red wine. Come and join us if you are in the area. Sending you lots of love! 
#tarietteevents #artisanfood #luberonwine #cheeseplatter #punintended #foodtasting #alliwantforvalentinesday #provencestyle #provencefood

There's nothing like a spot of haggling to start the day! We've spent this morning negotiating the best prices for Provence’s “black diamond”: the famed black winter truffle. A big thanks to Catherine and @latruffedeprovence for giving us access to France’s largest truffle market.
#wintertruffle #trufflemarket #blacktruffle #freshtruffles #truffesnoires #carpentrasprovencegourmande #truffesnoires #melanosporum

You may be familiar with the French "galette des rois", served on Jan 6th at the beginning of Epiphany. But in Provence, we do things differently. Have you heard of the Provençal "gateau des rois"? This brioche ring comes with a little gift hidden inside! Read more about this Provençal tradition, and why we love putting our new year's diet on hold for a few more days to enjoy the gateau des rois, on our blog, link in bio.
#gateaudesrois #epiphany #provencetradition #januarydiet #roismages #provencestyle #provencefood

Wishing you love, health and happiness for 2020. Happy New Year! .
.
#newyearswishes #2020goals #provencestyle #newyearinprovence

La crèche. 
One Christmas sight that defines the holiday for us. As a family from Provence, Christmas is a time for tradition and togetherness. Not one of big consumerism and excess (except for food and wine bien sûr!).
Read more about Thomas’ passion for santons, craftmanship, and the values of Christmas on our blog - link in bio.
#christmastraditions #shoplocal #lacreche #nativity #santonsdeprovence #christmasinprovence #supportsmallbusiness #artistsoninstagram

Black truffles for Black Friday
You are probably scrolling through hundreds of #blackfriday deals, offers and so on... None of them from us at Tariette. As a retailer, we categorically refuse to take part in this forced consumerism. We hate being preachy but today we want to speak out: PLEASE, when shopping today and until Christmas, remember to support small businesses and artisans! AVOID buying from big online retailers and instead hit the high streets and go to your local shops and markets. These people are the real backbone of our economy and play a big part in our cultures and traditions this and every holiday season. Picture credits and truffles sourced by our friends @latruffedeprovence
#supportsmallbusiness #shoplocal #blackfriday2019 #christmasshopping #supportartisans

Many of us will be watching the second episode of @chefrickstein new BBC series “Secret France” this evening. We are proud and a bit smug that Rick chose this beautiful villa to cook his new recipes. Maison Sebastien is located in the Alpes-de-Haute-Provence and it’s overlooking the Luberon. It’s only a few miles away from our hometown and very close to most of the producers we work with. Tune in on BBC2 tonight at 9pm.
#secretfrance #secretprovence #alpesdehauteprovence #provencestyle #visitalpesdehauteprovence #luberon #luberoncoeurdeprovence #tourismealpesdehauteprovence
picture by @_oliverstravels_

Personal, Tasteful, Delicious, Memorable.
Every Tariette hamper is unique. 
Add an artisan hamper from Provence to your Christmas list and get in touch. First, we’ll ask you a few questions to understand your preferences. Then, we’ll email you the description of our suggested hamper, including a picture. We take the utmost care over this, from the product selection to the finest details like the bow or the gift card. As a result, you can be sure that our hampers are personalised for the ones you love and tailored to your budget.
DM us or go to our website for more details!
#shopsmall #supportsmallbusiness #artisan #instashopsmall #christmashampers #personalisedgifts #provencefood #provencestyle

It’s only Tuesday, October feels like a neverending month and there’s so much work to do... We wished we could turn our phones off this morning, stay in bed - preferably this one at Neptune Reading - and eat croissants with our hazelnut praline spread...
#procastination #notamorningperson #onlyif #provencefood #provencestyle #frenchbreakfast #stayinginbed #lazytuesday #breakfastofchamps #neptunereading

CUTE STORY ALERT - Here’s our grandfather aka “Le Chef”, aged 92, carrying a bag of stale bread. Every Thursday, he disposes our left-over bread and sometimes food at the same spot in a forest near his home in Provence. Needless to say that many animals around are pretty happy about Le Chef’s weekly foodbank. All jokes aside, this video shows that not just the Greta Thunberg activists of this world care about protecting our planet and the animals. At a local level, the older generation quite often takes the lead when it comes to sustainable and environmental friendly habits. At least we do in our family!
#feedingtheanimals #reducingwaste #recyclingfood #environmentfriendly

Can’t beat the freshness of a fish bought straight off the fisherman’s boat - and the satifaction of arriving to the port early to get our hands on the best quality produce. 
On this rainy day here in the UK, we’d quite fancy a generous portion of a heart-warming fish soup for lunch, wouldn’t you?
#fishfriday #fbf #cassisforever #freshfish #freshofftheboat #mediterraneandiet #fishlover #foodiesofinstagram #fishmarket

Is it a cherry? Or, is it a tomato? 🤔
...
...
...
Answer: A cherry tomato in perfect disguise. It’s dark, delicious, organic and coming straight from a cute little farm shop in Cereste. Apparently, there are close to 500 different varieties of tomatoes grown in France!

Saturday morning = market day, and therefore the most exciting day of the week. The last week of August is a great time to come to Provence. The weather is hot and sunny (stormy at times), the kids are heading back to school, the market stalls are filled with delicious and riped summer fruits and vegs such as tomatoes, melons, apricots, peaches... And yet, autumn produce: grapes, mushrooms and stunning hydrangeas are already available to buy on the market... An epicurean’s heaven, really!
#provencemarket #marketday #farmersmarket #provencestyle  #provencefood

We are very proud to announce that our Hazelnut Praline Spread has won a Great Taste Award! Made by a small producer in the French Alps, it tastes delicious and indulgent. Our spread only contains hazelnuts and sugar. With no palm oil and no additives, we believe it’s better for you and the planet (than the other well known Italian hazelnut and cocoa spread). We love it on crêpes, bananas and vanilla ice cream. Its slightly runny texture makes it perfect to drizzle on food.
Our friend @patisseriemakesperfect crafts these scrumptious hazelnut praline choux using our product. We must admit making choux is a slightly more sophisticated and impressive way to enjoy our spread! Head to her blog to read her recipe. Google “patisserie makes perfect praline choux” to find her post. 
#greattasteawards2019 #greattasteawards #guildoffinefood #foodawards #hazelnutspread #hazelnutpraline #crepes

Meet Arthur.
Arthur is 102. He’s a fit and suave Lancashire gentleman. 
His secret to keep fit: he eats our food...
Note: this is not exactely accurate, we have just met Arthur at our food tasting in @neptune_chester. Arthur really is 102 and he is fond of our organic fruit coulis.
#foodtasting #foodtastingevent #provencestyle #frenchfood #provencefood #provencewines

Food I miss the most from Provence: #1 Tomatoes. They are the most consumed fruit or vegetable in France and it’s easy to see why! Whether you like them small or enormous, sweet or bitter, red, yellow, or even black, tomatoes are a staple in the markets of Provence. Those grown there are similar to those from many Mediterranean countries: plump, juicy and gorged on sunshine. 
It can be very challenging to find good tomatoes in the UK. My favourite British tomatoes come from the Isle of Wight, but they aren't quite the same as the ones from home—no offence UK tomato farmers! 
It doesn’t take much to elevate the simple Provence tomato to a delicious dish. In the summer (prime tomato season), I’ll often crave a meaty tomato with a drizzle of local extra virgin olive oil and some salt flakes from the Camargue, paired of course with a cool glass of rosé. The simple bare necessities! Thomas
#lovetomatoes #provencetomatoes #frenchtomatoes #tomatoseason #jaimelestomates #barenecessities #simplefood #farmersmarket #provencestyle #provencemarkets
